<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="424" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,319,416]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,319,344]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from all other subgenera by the combination of eyes naked, preoccipital carina absent laterally, and aroliae absent on all legs. In females the multidentate mandible with five to ten teeth (except four toothed only in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pasteels" authorityName="Pasteels" box="[180,418,391,416]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Pachyanthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micheneri">
<emphasis box="[180,319,391,416]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">P. micheneri</emphasis>
Pasteels
</taxonomicName>
) is unique. This subgenus is endemic to the Afrotropics.
</paragraph>
